(3, 'contact', '<p><span style="font-family:intro_bold">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Contacts</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family:intro_bold">Get in Touch!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-family:intro_bold">Got an awesome idea? For a FREE proposal and analysis of your needs, please shoot us an email at <span style="color:red">learnon.supp@gmail.com.</span> We&#39;ll contact you shortly!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style="font-family:intro_bold">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="http://images.clipartpanda.com/google-location-icon-location.png" style="height:20px" />&nbsp; Trg Lazara Ne&scaron;iÄ‡a 9, 24000 Subotica</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:intro_bold">&nbsp; <img src="http://bsccongress.com/im8/monochrome-red-phone-icon-clip-art.png" style="height:20px" />&nbsp; 024 / 551 - 972 or 024 / 552 - 031</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:intro_bold"><img src="http://www.360psg.com/content/images/icons/email-icon-fb-size.png" style="height:20px" />messc@tehnickaskolasubotica.edu.rs</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:intro_bold">&nbsp; <img src="http://www.rankalpha.biz/images/market_red.png" style="height:20px" />&nbsp;&nbsp; www.tehnickaskolasubotica.edu.rs</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family:intro_bold">learnon.supp@gmail.com</span></p>\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2016-01-04 00:16:19'),
(4, 'help', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong>Help</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1.Main page</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1.1 Accessibility</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The main page can be accessed from any other page on the website. All you have to do to access it is click on the LEARN_ON logo in the top left corner of the screen. You will also be redirected here when you log in, make a course etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1.2 Functionality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The main page serves a very important purpose.It is used to display all the published courses on the website. It also comes equipped with a quick search on the top of the screen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Categories</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2.1 Accessibility</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The categories page can be accessed only from the main page via link in the right &quot;tab&quot; below the search bar.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2.2 Functionality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>On the categories page there are 11 categories, each one links to a page in which you can see all the courses from that category (it also comes equipped with a quick search)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Account </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3.1 Accessibility</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The account page can be accessed from any other page on the website except from the course pages. The link is located in the menu on the left side of the screen.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3.2 Functionality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>On the account page you can change your: profile picture, password, email, username.You can also view your course stats and success rate as well as delete your account.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Library</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4.1 Accessibility</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The library page can be accessed from any other page on the website except from the course pages. The link is located in the menu on the left side of the screen.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4.2 Functionality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The library page is filled with all lectures from every course availableon the website. Just in case you want to see what the course is all about but you do not want to enroll just yet. You cane view all the lectures of a course simply by clicking on the course title and viewing the lecture list, then searching for them on the library page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Lecture</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4.1 Accessibility</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The lecture page is accessable only from the library page and the course page.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4.2 Functionality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A single lecture contains a title, a description, a PDF and an optional youtube video.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Course</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4.1 Accessibility</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The course page is accessable from any page in which you can see the course title, simply clicking on it will link you to the course page.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4.2 Functionality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>There are 2 types of course pages: Student and Guest</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Guest course page: On this page you can view the &quot;front page&quot; of the course with all of its lectures and the abillity to enroll.</li>\r\n	<li>Student course page: To have access to this page you simply have to be enrolled in the given course. From this page you have the abillity to read all of the courses lectures, you have the abillity to quit the course and take the final test after wich you will finish the course.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Test</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4.1 Accessibility</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A test page canonly be accessed from the student version of the course page.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>4.2 Functionality</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>When on this page you have an unlimited amount of time to answer all the questions. When you are certain that you checked the correct answers press the <em>SAVE </em>button and move on to the next question, when you answer all the questions you possibly can simply exit the page to finish the course. You will be given 1 point for each correct answer and 1 point will be taken from you for each uncorrect gues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2016-01-08 18:59:15');

